01:12:44,200 --> 01:12:48,876
Ten minutes past graduation, I'm gone!
To freedom!

971
01:12:49,680 --> 01:12:51,113
For everyone.

972
01:12:52,640 --> 01:12:54,278
Now, this is the plan.

973
01:12:54,360 --> 01:12:57,238
As soon as school is finished,
we move to Utah.

974
01:12:57,760 --> 01:12:58,875
Utah?

975
01:13:00,080 --> 01:13:02,674
I thought you'd be going to Paris
or New York.

976
01:13:02,760 --> 01:13:03,875
What's in Utah?

977
01:13:03,960 --> 01:13:08,511
Rita. I met her last summer. She's cool.
You'll really dig her.

978
01:13:08,880 --> 01:13:13,635
She's got this little cabin outside the hills
of Provo where she raises chickens.

979
01:13:13,960 --> 01:13:17,748
I'll write, and you two can take care
of the chickens to support us.

980
01:13:18,120 --> 01:13:20,839
- I can't do that.
- Why not?

981
01:13:21,040 --> 01:13:22,758
Polygamy's legal in Utah.

982
01:13:24,040 --> 01:13:25,871
I'm allergic to chickens.

983
01:13:31,600 --> 01:13:34,751
Wait. What about the other night?

984
01:13:35,560 --> 01:13:38,711
We were like two stars
in the same constellation.

985
01:13:40,120 --> 01:13:44,796
Michael, you and I are light-years apart.
You should go, but not with me.

986
01:13:44,880 --> 01:13:49,590
But we had heat, baby. Passion! Fire!

987
01:13:50,520 --> 01:13:53,637
We owe it to ourselves to fuse together.

988
01:13:54,680 --> 01:13:56,591
At least one more time.

989
01:13:57,520 --> 01:14:00,830
That's a great line.
You are going to be a terrific writer.

990
01:14:02,840 --> 01:14:05,513
- You think so?
- Yeah.

991
01:14:06,520 --> 01:14:11,514
Michael,
we had one glorious night together.

992
01:14:12,200 --> 01:14:15,033
Someday you'll remember
and write about it.

993
01:14:17,240 --> 01:14:18,355
Yeah.

994
01:14:19,960 --> 01:14:20,949
I can dig that.

995
01:14:23,080 --> 01:14:24,991
Bittersweet perfection.

996
01:14:25,760 --> 01:14:29,992
Dogs of lust on leashes of memory. Yes!

997
01:14:33,000 --> 01:14:34,433
It's Charlie.

998
01:14:34,880 --> 01:14:36,313
What a treat.

999
01:14:39,760 --> 01:14:40,909
Now I get it.

1000
01:14:41,520 --> 01:14:42,919
It's great.

1001
01:14:44,280 --> 01:14:47,477
Peggy Sue's still stuck on
"Treble Without a Cause."

1002
01:14:48,040 --> 01:14:49,951
Come on, I want to dance.

1003
01:15:09,880 --> 01:15:12,394
I thought I knew everything about him.

1004
01:15:12,720 --> 01:15:14,233
Can we split now?

1005
01:15:42,440 --> 01:15:43,759
Thank you.

1006
01:15:46,720 --> 01:15:48,915
So, Mr. Wilkins, new client?

1007
01:15:50,120 --> 01:15:51,792
I'm sorry, Charlie.

1008
01:15:55,280 --> 01:15:57,350
I don't think so, you know.

1009
01:15:58,680 --> 01:16:00,875
It happens, but not with you.

1010
01:16:01,160 --> 01:16:02,718
Believe me when I tell you.

1011
01:16:02,800 --> 01:16:05,360
Maybe it's the material.
But it can't happen.

1012
01:16:29,000 --> 01:16:30,228
Good morning.

1013
01:16:33,240 --> 01:16:34,673
Charlie?

1014
01:16:43,760 --> 01:16:45,716
What are you doing here?

1015
01:16:46,160 --> 01:16:48,116
I wanted to talk to you.

1016
01:16:48,560 --> 01:16:51,996
I've got one last thing
I have to do at school and then<i>...</i>

1017
01:16:53,120 --> 01:16:56,396
Elvis. Hi. How are you? Hi, guy.

1018
01:16:56,480 --> 01:16:58,550
Elvis is dead. That's Ajax.

1019
01:17:01,320 --> 01:17:03,470
I guess I always liked Elvis.

1020
01:17:04,320 --> 01:17:06,709
- Can I have a ride to school?
- No.

1021
01:17:07,080 --> 01:17:10,595
- Why?
- The tiger's out of commission for a while.

1022
01:17:10,840 --> 01:17:11,875
Come on.

1023
01:17:12,120 --> 01:17:16,159
- How about a walk, Charlie Bell?
- How did you know about that?

1024
01:17:16,320 --> 01:17:18,709
I was at Lena's last night.
I heard you sing.

1025
01:17:18,800 --> 01:17:20,438
I thought you were terrific.

1026
01:17:20,520 --> 01:17:23,114
Not terrific enough.
What were you doing there?

1027
01:17:23,200 --> 01:17:25,919
- Who were you with?
- Well, what were you doing there?

1028
01:17:26,000 --> 01:17:28,195
You never told me you sang
with an R & B group.

1029
01:17:28,280 --> 01:17:32,159
There's not a whole heck of a lot
we know about each other, Peggy.

1030
01:17:33,480 --> 01:17:37,712
- I forgot how much music meant to you.
- That's real big of you.

1031
01:17:38,160 --> 01:17:40,390
Stop being so defensive. Here.

1032
01:17:41,520 --> 01:17:43,431
I wrote a song for you.

1033
01:17:45,120 --> 01:17:48,749
- Why did you write me a song?
- Because I want to help you.

1034
01:17:50,280 --> 01:17:54,114
- It'll be a hit. I promise.
- Come on! Stop being sarcastic.

1035
01:17:54,720 --> 01:17:57,393
Lee Wilkins came to hear me last night.

1036
01:17:57,640 --> 01:18:00,234
He told me to forget it.

1037
01:18:02,200 --> 01:18:04,270
Would you just take a look at it?

1038
01:18:04,720 --> 01:18:06,870
Come on. I wrote it for you.

1039
01:18:07,840 --> 01:18:11,116
Well, if you wrote it I guess I'll look at it.

1040
01:18:13,720 --> 01:18:17,190
Listen, about the other night,
I feel so stupid.

1041
01:18:18,280 --> 01:18:22,671
I'm beginning to think that maybe
there is more to life than just music.

1042
01:18:24,520 --> 01:18:28,911
Do you think the world would still like me
if I stopped being Mr. Excitement?

1043
01:18:31,880 --> 01:18:32,995
Yeah.

1044
01:18:35,040 --> 01:18:37,235
Do you want to walk to school?

1045
01:18:37,880 --> 01:18:40,030
Okay, I'll just put the dog inside.

1046
01:18:40,680 --> 01:18:41,954
Come on, Ajax.

1047
01:18:45,680 --> 01:18:48,478
What's the matter, princess?
Lost your prince?

1048
01:18:49,800 --> 01:18:53,509
Delores, there are a lot of things
I could say to you...

1049
01:18:53,680 --> 01:18:56,069
...but you're just not worth the effort.

1050
01:18:57,360 --> 01:19:01,956
- I'm so sorry. These pens are so tricky, I<i>...</i>
- You did that on purpose!

1051
01:19:02,600 --> 01:19:06,149
I hate you! Go stuff your bra!

1052
01:19:06,880 --> 01:19:10,555
- I beg your pardon?
- Take a long walk on a short pier.

1053
01:19:11,000 --> 01:19:12,592
Have a nice day.

1054
01:19:25,720 --> 01:19:29,759
You know, Peggy, there are so many things
to look forward to in the future.

1055
01:19:33,920 --> 01:19:35,831
I came to say good-bye, Richard.

1056
01:19:35,920 --> 01:19:39,117
Good-bye? Wait a minute. Sit down.

1057
01:19:40,680 --> 01:19:45,117
Good-bye? Where are you going?
Peggy, we have a partnership here.

1058
01:19:45,200 --> 01:19:48,749
- I'm making progress on that microchip.
- Well, you were meant to.

1059
01:19:48,840 --> 01:19:51,354
You're one of the people
good things happen to.

1060
01:19:51,440 --> 01:19:52,589
So are you.

1061
01:19:52,920 --> 01:19:55,798
- You have a vision, Peggy.
- A vision?

1062
01:19:56,840 --> 01:19:58,910
I am a walking anachronism!

1063
01:19:59,920 --> 01:20:03,151
I've upset my parents. I miss my kids.

1064
01:20:03,440 --> 01:20:07,194
I could be trapped here forever.
And poor Charlie.

1065
01:20:07,360 --> 01:20:11,194
I got pregnant when I was 18.
That was why we had to get married.

1066
01:20:11,640 --> 01:20:13,153
Tomorrow's my birthday.

1067
01:20:13,240 --> 01:20:16,755
- I have to get out of here.
- You broke up with Charlie?

1068
01:20:17,840 --> 01:20:20,229
Yeah. I know it's a gamble.

1069
01:20:20,960 --> 01:20:23,315
I've loved him for a long, long time.

1070
01:20:23,440 --> 01:20:26,557
Okay. Then let's do something
really visionary.

1071
01:20:26,840 --> 01:20:29,115
Change your destiny, Peggy Sue.

1072
01:20:29,760 --> 01:20:33,116
Change your destiny and marry me.

1073
01:20:34,760 --> 01:20:39,231
No! Peggy Sue got married.

1074
01:20:39,760 --> 01:20:41,159
Case closed.

1075
01:20:41,880 --> 01:20:44,474
I don't want to marry anyone, Richard.

1076
01:20:45,000 --> 01:20:45,989
Good-bye.

1077
01:20:46,280 --> 01:20:48,669
Wait! Peggy, please. Can I go with you?

1078
01:20:48,760 --> 01:20:51,911
No! You have to be valedictorian.

1079
01:20:58,840 --> 01:21:00,831
Peggy Sue, wait a minute!

1080
01:21:01,280 --> 01:21:04,590
Listen, I cut shop
and I did some work on your song.

1081
01:21:05,520 --> 01:21:07,954
You know, it's not half bad
for your first try.

1082
01:21:08,040 --> 01:21:11,112
I changed all the "yeahs" to "oohs,"
but listen to this:

1083
01:21:11,200 --> 01:21:14,590
"She loves you, ooh, ooh, ooh
You love me, ooh, ooh, ooh"

1084
01:21:16,240 --> 01:21:17,389
I got to go.

1085
01:21:17,480 --> 01:21:20,995
About your birthday.
I made reservations at Chez Trev.

1086
01:21:21,360 --> 01:21:24,238
I thought it would be great to eat
at a nice restaurant.

1087
01:21:24,320 --> 01:21:25,912
I won't be here.

1088
01:21:26,400 --> 01:21:29,551
- Why?
- I want to go see my grandparents.

1089
01:21:30,600 --> 01:21:32,238
Good-bye, Charlie.

1090
01:21:33,120 --> 01:21:35,588
I cancelled the tickets for Fabian.

1091
01:22:21,880 --> 01:22:22,949
Close that.

1092
01:22:23,040 --> 01:22:24,758
- There you are.
- Thank you.

1093
01:22:26,680 --> 01:22:30,309
Look! Oh, it's so beautiful.

1094
01:23:03,800 --> 01:23:07,156
What's the matter, Peggy?
Someone jump on your grave?

1095
01:23:14,440 --> 01:23:18,274
You know, Peggy, your mother said
you had a dream that I died.

1096
01:23:19,080 --> 01:23:20,911
I wish she hadn't have told you that.

1097
01:23:21,000 --> 01:23:24,788
I'm not afraid.
I know exactly when I'm going to die.

1098
01:23:24,880 --> 01:23:28,395
What's it going to be, Lizzy?
Seventy-five or eighty?

1099
01:23:29,400 --> 01:23:30,992
I'm not telling!

1100
01:23:31,080 --> 01:23:33,958
I've been trying to drag
that out of her for years.

1101
01:23:34,120 --> 01:23:36,918
You know,
dreams are a fascinating business.

1102
01:23:37,040 --> 01:23:41,033
- Especially when you see the future.
- Do you believe all this?

1103
01:23:41,360 --> 01:23:45,433
Well, I like to speculate.
Like this book I'm reading right now.

1104
01:23:45,520 --> 01:23:50,514
It's about a woman in Colorado who says
she lived in Ireland 150 years ago.

1105
01:23:51,200 --> 01:23:54,033
She gives names,
dates and where she lived.

1106
01:23:55,360 --> 01:23:56,998
Grandma. Grandpa.

1107
01:23:59,000 --> 01:24:01,070
I want to tell you something.

1108
01:24:05,520 --> 01:24:09,229
If you believe it, darling, then I believe.

1109
01:24:10,240 --> 01:24:13,232
Being young is just as confusing
as being old.

1110
01:24:14,400 --> 01:24:16,914
The things that happened to me
50 years ago...

1111
01:24:17,000 --> 01:24:20,151
...are more on my mind
than the things that happen today.

1112
01:24:21,120 --> 01:24:23,395
But I'm remembering the future.

1113
01:24:25,160 --> 01:24:27,116
A chilling wind tonight.

1114
01:24:28,720 --> 01:24:30,358
It's really picking up.

1115
01:24:30,440 --> 01:24:33,989
Right now,
you're just browsing through time.

1116
01:24:36,000 --> 01:24:38,594
Choose the things you'll be proud of.

1117
01:24:39,040 --> 01:24:40,678
Things that last.

1118
01:24:41,720 --> 01:24:43,711
I'm proud of my children.

1119
01:24:44,120 --> 01:24:45,872
I miss them so much.

1120
01:24:46,320 --> 01:24:48,993
Scott and Beth.

1121
01:24:50,480 --> 01:24:52,391
I named my daughter after you.

1122
01:24:54,920 --> 01:24:58,310
Sweetheart, thank you.

1123
01:25:04,600 --> 01:25:05,828
Grandpa.

1124
01:25:08,840 --> 01:25:11,718
When you and Grandma are gone,
the family's gone.

1125
01:25:11,800 --> 01:25:13,791
And I'll never see the cousins anymore.

1126
01:25:13,880 --> 01:25:17,668
It's your grandma's strudel
that's kept this family together.

1127
01:25:17,960 --> 01:25:22,078
If you could do it all again, Grandpa,
what would you do different?

1128
01:25:22,680 --> 01:25:25,353
I'd have taken better care of my teeth.

1129
01:25:26,080 --> 01:25:29,117
Now what's Peggy Sue going to do
at your lodge meeting?

1130
01:25:30,360 --> 01:25:33,272
It's her 18th birthday
and I want to show her off.

1131
01:25:33,440 --> 01:25:36,989
It was my idea, Grandma.
I wondered about those lodge meetings.

1132
01:25:37,080 --> 01:25:39,435
He won't tell me.
But I have my suspicions.

1133
01:25:39,520 --> 01:25:41,750
I don't want to know.
Have a good time, darling.

1134
01:25:41,840 --> 01:25:43,159
All right.

1135
01:25:45,040 --> 01:25:47,349
- Good-bye.
- Good-bye, darling.

1136
01:25:48,800 --> 01:25:50,028
Grandpa?

1137
01:25:50,360 --> 01:25:53,079
What does Grandma think you do
at these meetings?

1138
01:25:53,160 --> 01:25:54,991
Stag movies and poker.

1139
01:26:01,240 --> 01:26:04,710
I may be an old fool,
but I think I can help you.

1140
01:26:06,280 --> 01:26:09,158
At least I got to see you
and Grandma again.

1141
01:26:10,040 --> 01:26:12,190
Has this ever worked before?

1142
01:26:12,320 --> 01:26:17,110
The last time was 600 years ago.
And it's about time for another one.

1143
01:26:44,000 --> 01:26:46,116
Welcome, Peggy Sue!

1144
01:26:46,600 --> 01:26:49,672
Peggy Sue! Welcome, Peggy Sue!

1145
01:26:49,800 --> 01:26:52,678
- It's so wonderful to have you here with us.
- Thank you.

1146
01:26:52,760 --> 01:26:56,355
You've come to the right place.
Our lodge was founded by a time traveller.

1147
01:26:56,440 --> 01:26:58,874
- We're going to send you back home.
- That's right!

1148
01:26:58,960 --> 01:27:01,155
You know, this is very exciting for all of us.

1149
01:27:01,240 --> 01:27:05,472
You know, we've waited a long time
to find a girl like you.

1150
01:27:05,600 --> 01:27:06,669
Yes!

1151
01:27:06,760 --> 01:27:10,673
Grandpa! Do you have to wear that hat?

1152
01:27:11,040 --> 01:27:12,678
Wouldn't be a lodge without hats.

1153
01:28:07,160 --> 01:28:08,957
"Lord of the universe.

1154
01:28:10,000 --> 01:28:11,752
"Vast and mighty one.

1155
01:28:12,520 --> 01:28:14,033
"Ruler of light.

1156
01:28:15,080 --> 01:28:16,672
"King of the sun.

1157
01:28:16,960 --> 01:28:19,872
"This girl is lost amid your mysteries...

1158
01:28:19,960 --> 01:28:22,599
"...and wishes to return to her own time.

1159
01:28:23,040 --> 01:28:26,032
"We adore thee and invoke thee!

1160
01:28:26,440 --> 01:28:28,032
"Grant thine aid.

1161
01:28:28,560 --> 01:28:33,350
"Look with favour upon us
as we witness the regeneration of spirit.

1162
01:28:35,120 --> 01:28:36,872
"We ask thy intervention...

1163
01:28:36,960 --> 01:28:41,909
"...that this girl may return to thee
on the wings of thy love."

1164
01:28:43,760 --> 01:28:48,038
"Womb of the mother,
reclaim thy child of light."

1165
01:28:48,600 --> 01:28:50,989
"The name of your love is rebirth."

1166
01:28:51,440 --> 01:28:54,318
- This is never going to work.
- It's going to work!

1167
01:28:54,400 --> 01:28:57,198
"Reclaim thy child of light."

1168
01:28:57,280 --> 01:29:02,274
"We offer up this girl
that her soul may find its home."

1169
01:29:10,600 --> 01:29:15,355
It's nothing to worry about.
Somebody get the lights.

1170
01:29:17,080 --> 01:29:19,435
Somebody get the lights!

1171
01:29:22,360 --> 01:29:23,395
She's gone!

1172
01:29:25,680 --> 01:29:28,114
What the hell do you think you're doing?

1173
01:29:28,560 --> 01:29:31,552
I'm saving you!
They were going to vaporise you!

1174
01:29:31,640 --> 01:29:35,997
Don't be ridiculous! They're harmless
old men! My grandfather was in there!

1175
01:29:36,080 --> 01:29:38,548
- Get in the car!
- I'm not getting in this monstrosity!

1176
01:29:38,840 --> 01:29:40,671
Well, the girl's gone.

1177
01:29:40,960 --> 01:29:42,598
Let's play cards.

1178
01:29:54,720 --> 01:29:58,235
I've got good news.
Now sit down right here.

1179
01:29:58,560 --> 01:30:00,073
You've got two minutes!

1180
01:30:00,160 --> 01:30:02,993
I told my father
that I'm going to quit singing.

1181
01:30:03,080 --> 01:30:06,868
And he gave me 10 percent
of the business right now!

1182
01:30:06,960 --> 01:30:10,475
- What are you talking about?
- I know what you've been going through.

1183
01:30:10,560 --> 01:30:12,596
You were just scared.

1184
01:30:12,760 --> 01:30:16,435
But you don't have to be scared anymore.
I can support you now.

1185
01:30:16,520 --> 01:30:18,670
- Shit!
- Peggy Sue?

1186
01:30:19,920 --> 01:30:21,638
Will you marry me?

1187
01:30:21,720 --> 01:30:23,950
How can you know
what I've been going through?

1188
01:30:24,040 --> 01:30:27,350
Of course I'm scared!
I can't change anything.

1189
01:30:27,440 --> 01:30:29,795
- I can't help anybody.
- You're not listening to me.

1190
01:30:29,880 --> 01:30:32,235
- I'm proposing to you now.
- You betrayed me.

1191
01:30:32,320 --> 01:30:34,515
You were never there for me
and the children.

1192
01:30:34,600 --> 01:30:38,513
I'll be there for the children.
I'll forget Walter.

1193
01:30:38,960 --> 01:30:42,475
Forget the group. I want to marry you!

1194
01:30:42,720 --> 01:30:43,869
Don't be crazy.

1195
01:30:43,960 --> 01:30:47,714
I may be crazy, but I'm not crazy enough
to marry you twice.

1196
01:30:49,560 --> 01:30:50,834
Christ.

1197
01:30:52,560 --> 01:30:53,788
Peggy.

1198
01:30:57,040 --> 01:30:58,439
I'm sorry.

1199
01:31:02,360 --> 01:31:05,909
I thought I was what you wanted me to be.

1200
01:31:07,400 --> 01:31:09,072
It's all my fault.

1201
01:31:14,400 --> 01:31:15,515
Here.

1202
01:31:16,920 --> 01:31:18,876
It's a birthday present.

1203
01:31:20,360 --> 01:31:23,113
I'm tired of being the romantic fool.

1204
01:31:24,520 --> 01:31:26,636
I'm going to go save my car.

1205
01:31:28,120 --> 01:31:29,348
Charlie?

1206
01:31:32,680 --> 01:31:34,159
It opens, too.

1207
01:31:34,640 --> 01:31:36,039
Look inside.

1208
01:31:41,920 --> 01:31:45,230
Scott and Beth. Where did you get this?

1209
01:31:45,760 --> 01:31:47,671
Who are Scott and Beth?

1210
01:31:48,840 --> 01:31:51,195
Your mother gave me those.
It's you and me.

1211
01:31:51,280 --> 01:31:52,759
You know that.

1212
01:31:54,760 --> 01:31:58,514
So are they.

1213
01:31:59,800 --> 01:32:01,472
I do love you.

1214
01:32:02,120 --> 01:32:03,473
I love you.

1215
01:32:06,600 --> 01:32:08,591
This is right, Peggy Sue.

1216
01:32:10,600 --> 01:32:12,636
I want this to be forever.

1217
01:32:20,600 --> 01:32:22,352
<i>Mom, can you hear me?</i>

1218
01:32:24,640 --> 01:32:26,517
<i>Please, Mom, can you hear me?</i>

1219
01:32:26,600 --> 01:32:28,477
<i>They call what happened a near-death...</i>

1220
01:32:28,560 --> 01:32:31,120
<i>... but we figured out</i>
<i>exactly what the problem is...</i>

1221
01:32:31,200 --> 01:32:33,191
<i>You are a very lucky young lady!</i>

1222
01:32:33,360 --> 01:32:36,432
<i>What happened to you, Peggy Sue,</i>
<i>was a very rare problem...</i>

1223
01:32:36,520 --> 01:32:38,272
<i>... with the rhythm of your heart.</i>

1224
01:32:38,360 --> 01:32:39,839
<i>Mom, do you remember anything?</i>

1225
01:32:39,920 --> 01:32:43,913
<i>In fact, at the party,</i>
<i>they had to do CPR on you...</i>

1226
01:32:45,000 --> 01:32:48,709
<i>... before the paramedics arrived</i>
<i>to give your heart a shock and restart it.</i>

1227
01:32:48,840 --> 01:32:50,876
<i>Dad's been here every day.</i>

1228
01:32:51,200 --> 01:32:53,475
<i>"'Cause I love you, Peggy Sue</i>

1229
01:32:58,400 --> 01:33:01,870
"I love you, girl, and I need you, Peggy"

1230
01:33:09,480 --> 01:33:10,833
Charlie?

1231
01:33:12,240 --> 01:33:16,153
- Was I dead?
- I thought you were for a while.

1232
01:33:18,360 --> 01:33:19,839
You look awful.

1233
01:33:20,360 --> 01:33:23,033
You look like you haven't slept in days.

1234
01:33:24,120 --> 01:33:27,157
- You look so old.
- But happy.

1235
01:33:28,400 --> 01:33:30,470
Very happy, Peggy.

1236
01:33:31,640 --> 01:33:34,916
I thought I knew everything about you.
I'm sorry.

1237
01:33:35,000 --> 01:33:37,036
I wanted to tell you that I<i>...</i>

1238
01:33:37,120 --> 01:33:39,236
- I wanted to...
- I'm sorry.

1239
01:33:39,360 --> 01:33:43,433
I can't live without you.

1240
01:33:46,440 --> 01:33:48,078
What about Janet?

1241
01:33:51,400 --> 01:33:55,234
That's over.
I got tired of translating everything to her.

1242
01:33:55,320 --> 01:33:58,153
She thought the Big Bopper
was a hamburger.

1243
01:34:02,880 --> 01:34:05,872
- Who are all the flowers from?
- Everyone.

1244
01:34:06,480 --> 01:34:10,155
Maddy and Arthur, Carol and Walter...

1245
01:34:11,280 --> 01:34:13,111
...Richard Norvik.

1246
01:34:14,200 --> 01:34:18,955
And here's a book by that guy
in high school, Michael Fitzsimmons.

1247
01:34:19,880 --> 01:34:21,791
He dedicated it to you.

1248
01:34:27,360 --> 01:34:29,635
It couldn't be me. I hardly knew him.

1249
01:34:33,520 --> 01:34:35,750
I'll just set this right here.

1250
01:34:40,320 --> 01:34:42,550
I had a strange experience.

1251
01:34:43,760 --> 01:34:47,594
I went back to high school
and I spent a lot of time with you.

1252
01:34:48,960 --> 01:34:53,317
You and Walter and Leon were singing
<i>I Wonder Why.</i>

1253
01:34:53,960 --> 01:34:55,473
God! Dion!

1254
01:34:56,120 --> 01:34:57,792
You were terrific.

1255
01:34:59,120 --> 01:35:01,918
And I kept trying to push you away.

1256
01:35:03,200 --> 01:35:06,317
- But you wouldn't give up.
- I'll never give up.

1257
01:35:08,120 --> 01:35:09,792
Would you hold me?

1258
01:35:14,080 --> 01:35:19,108
I don't expect that all our problems
can just vanish.

1259
01:35:21,800 --> 01:35:25,679
Christ, I would cut my right arm off
for another chance.

1260
01:35:25,760 --> 01:35:29,389
No, please, I need some time.

1261
01:35:41,600 --> 01:35:43,989
Well, I'll let you get some rest.

1262
01:35:54,240 --> 01:35:58,199
I'd like to invite you over to our house
for dinner on Sunday.

1263
01:35:58,920 --> 01:36:00,433
With your kids.

1264
01:36:03,960 --> 01:36:05,632
I'll make a strudel.

